This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically deals with natural language processing. The second likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper evaluates different sentence encoders. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with machine learning models. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper uses neural networks for sentence encoding. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper uses Wikipedia as a source of data, which is often used in computer vision research.
